																		Author&#039;s Note
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2005044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250575" alt="Decibelles" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2005044)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;" >Decibelles</a></span> <span class="odate time_1431041508 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 May 2015 23:31</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2288256">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Its anomalous condition continues to deteriorate. By current estimates, the Foundation will have lost it by 20██-██</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Before I edit this further; I listened to an album called <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLzqAcVhDrXVlm74AfAXseV84sjKg0lasi">Music From the Penguin Club Orchestra</a> exclusively when writing this. Give it a listen. It's great. The song <em><a href="https://youtu.be/-XvPdwHsjhQ?list=PLzqAcVhDrXVlm74AfAXseV84sjKg0lasi">The Sound Of Someone You Love Who's Going Away And It Doesn't Matter</a></em>, in particular, helped a ton to set the mood. Give it a go!</p>
<p>Okay, so this is a tale about <a href="/scp-1467">SCP-1467</a>, which was featured last. Thanks to thedeadlymoose, TwistedGears, and Scantron for reading the first two sections when I originally wrote it and showed it to them. Without their approval and encouragement, I would not have continued to write this.</p>
<p>Huge thanks to Cimmerian and qntm for informing where to go with this and how to improve it such. I didn't take all of their suggestions, or even that much, but they helped me make it better, I believe.</p>
<p>Thanks to TwistedGears, Dmatix, and snorlison for proofreading as well and correcting stuff. Also thanks to thedeadlymoose, who'll inevitably rip me apart for whatever poor grammar or structure I have XD</p>
<p>Finally, thanks to everyone in #site19 who read it and said they liked it!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;I&nbsp;admittedly&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;secret&nbsp;ambition&nbsp;with&nbsp;this&nbsp;tale.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;I&nbsp;admittedly&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;secret&nbsp;ambition&nbsp;with&nbsp;this&nbsp;tale.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I want to at least get half of the votes for this tale that 1467 does, cause I'm ambitious like that.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;I&nbsp;admittedly&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;secret&nbsp;ambition&nbsp;with&nbsp;this&nbsp;tale.</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Ported&nbsp;from&nbsp;my&nbsp;author&nbsp;page&nbsp;discussion&nbsp;thread.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This is obstinately a tale about <a href="/scp-1467">SCP-1467</a>. And it wholly is, but it's a lot more.</p>
<p>I published this May 7, 2015. In truth, it was being written for years. This is where my fascination with writing about mental health is at its most obvious. The reason why I connect and love 1467 so much is because it's real easy to read it as a metaphor for&#8230; a lot. It's up to reader interpretation, I suppose. I'll spare you how I view it; what's important is the writing. I wrote this a week or two after I broke up with my girlfriend in April. The first part of the tale was all I wrote, and it was done in a hurry one night. <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1506814023" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;">thedeadlymoose</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1506814023" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=617958&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1506814023" alt="Communism will win" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=617958)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;">Communism will win</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1735681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1506814023" alt="TwistedGears" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1735681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span> all liked it and encouraged me to continue, so I did. Over the course of three nights (one of those being an all-nighter), I wrote and wrote and wrote and edited this like you could not believe. It shows; only someone who's mad would write an article that essentially treats its audience like their therapist.</p>
<p>I love prose that's off-kilter, purple and normal, grounded in reality but ever so fanciful. It immediately represents a viewpoint that comes from two different places at once, even if it shares a common origin (in this case, the third-person view of Mr. Smith), which I think helps establish the mood I'm going for. It's, in essence, a story about being lost and losing yourself. It's a feeling most can relate to, but especially people with mental illness like myself, so I had to make it as universal as I could. And I did I think. I pulled it off real well.</p>
<p>The only reason why this doesn't surpass 3090 for me is because Smith isn't an original character. I adapted a character with gaps in his story and then constructed a personal narrative around. This is the challenge inherent to this site in writing tales about characters in other tales or SCPs. This is a story, by the way, that could have only been written and published in a certain period of my life. It was either then or never. I'll never write a story like this again, nor would I want to. It's the manifestation of emotions and expressions I only could have gotten out then. But if I were totally normal and still happily dating, would it be worth not having this story? Yes, it would.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

